Media Release: Update on the coronavirus by Premier Alan Winde 17 February 2021 As of 1pm on 17 February, the Western Cape has 5215 active Covid-19 infections with a total of 272 817 confirmed Covid-19 cases and 256 817 recoveries. Total confirmed COVID-19 cases 272 817 Total recoveries 256 817 Total deaths 10 962 Total active cases (currently infected patients) 5215 Tests conducted 1296533 Hospitalisations 1427 with 317 in ICU or high care The Western Cape has recorded 23 additional deaths, bringing the total number of COVID-19 related deaths in the province to10 962. We send our condolences to their loved ones at this time. Additional data is available on the Western Cape Covid-19 data dashboard which also features active cases per sub-district, active cases per 100 000 and 7-day moving averages. Access the data dashboard here: https://coronavirus.westerncape.gov.za/covid-19-dashboard State of the Province Address: Earlier today, I delivered my State of the Province Address in Genadendal. The full speech is available here: https://www.westerncape.gov.za/speech/state-province-address-2021 and the statement detailing the major announcements I made to address Covid-19, and to save jobs, create safer communities and advance dignity and wellbeing here: https://www.westerncape.gov.za/gc-news/97/56077. Issued by Western Cape Office of the Premier, 17 February 2021